12:47.000 --> 12:50.120
Here she tells us about the rather unique source of inspiration.

13:18.460 --> 13:23.460
This cockroach came crawling down the side of the house and it sat there and it looked at me.

13:24.980 --> 13:28.060
Your first reaction with a cockroach is smash it.

13:28.760 --> 13:31.380
But I decided to sit there and look at it.

13:31.940 --> 13:34.560
It's really interesting, the creature.

13:34.760 --> 13:36.720
Actually it's pretty in its way.

13:37.500 --> 13:41.760
Very nice lines, very bright black eyes, little alert.

13:42.360 --> 13:44.980
And it just sat there and we looked at each other for a while.

13:46.180 --> 13:48.940
So I decided to write a story about a cockroach.

13:49.780 --> 13:52.020
And I decided that it's going to be Fantasy.

13:54.300 --> 13:55.940
It just seemed to fit in Fantasy.

13:56.260 --> 14:07.000
So that cockroach ended up, I believe, with about ten pages out of 300 or something like that.

14:07.700 --> 14:08.900
But he was in there.

14:08.900 --> 14:10.480
He was by inspiration.

14:11.660 --> 14:14.680
And I don't know, he just felt like writing Fantasy.

14:16.340 --> 14:18.900
It wasn't any great momentous decision.

14:19.120 --> 14:20.040
It's just the way it turned out.

14:44.800 --> 14:48.280
The Cockroach passage, by the way, is in the first novel in the series, Moon Gather.

14:48.820 --> 14:54.080
Sometimes Fantasy is criticized as being someone easier to write than Science Fiction because there are no rules to break.

14:54.520 --> 14:57.480
Right, Science Fiction takes place in the world of consistent logic.

14:57.740 --> 15:00.460
Whereas in Fantasy one can resort to magic when things appear hopeless.

15:01.000 --> 15:03.420
If clumsily handled, such antics can irritate the reader.

15:03.760 --> 15:06.900
Clayton told us, though, that she believes well-written Fantasy follows rules.

15:07.900 --> 15:17.220
I am one of those who really believes that there are rules to magic.

15:17.540 --> 15:22.700
I don't believe in magic at all, but it's fun to play with.

15:23.560 --> 15:36.140
It's sort of an extension of all the psionics, which is probably present is not a science either.

15:36.140 --> 15:41.420
Might be, but many people are skeptical about that.

15:42.340 --> 15:47.640
But I can't...

15:47.640 --> 15:52.900
It is just the same thing in the sense that writing Science Fiction,

15:53.580 --> 16:02.540
only you write in other terms the same kind of rulekeeping.

16:06.520 --> 16:21.680
The societies, you can play with visual things and possibilities in a different way.

16:22.640 --> 16:27.560
It's not more at least in Science Fiction, if you do it properly, I think.

16:28.300 --> 16:32.420
It just has a different set of assumptions.

16:34.180 --> 16:36.560
And it's fun to play with those assumptions.

16:37.920 --> 16:42.120
So, Fantasy or Science Fiction, Joe Clayton's carefully crafted work is worth reading.

