25:19.780 --> 25:24.780
and certainly did not attract the larger audience with the Fire Dancer series.

25:26.260 --> 25:27.300
They're just different books.

25:28.500 --> 25:34.020
The Fire Dancer series is built around the relationship between Reba, a Senyan dancer, and her Brynn mentor, Kyrton.

25:34.560 --> 25:36.960
Reba is a young dancer who literally commands energy.

25:36.960 --> 25:40.140
When she dances, the energy streams from her as if it were fire.

25:40.340 --> 25:44.720
Kyrton, who is of an alien species, helps Reba learn to control and modulate her powers.

25:45.280 --> 25:50.280
Reba and Kyrton are among the last of their respective races, and they are attempting in the series to locate other survivors.

25:50.700 --> 25:57.000
Since it's not spelled out in the series, we asked Maxwell to tell us how the relationship between the dancers and the Brynn might have evolved.

25:57.000 --> 26:01.320
They are constructs as the construct in that sense.

26:01.480 --> 26:11.040
In other words, we are talking about a universe in which what we would call a human or whatever you want to call it is not new.

26:11.620 --> 26:13.440
It has evolved independently.

26:13.960 --> 26:17.240
It has evolved with self-force evolution.

26:17.580 --> 26:22.320
It has evolved in other people's labs against their will.

26:22.320 --> 26:29.660
This is not a world in which logic, as we understand it, biology is always going to be followed through.

26:30.060 --> 26:36.580
It is simply a universe in which that which could survive and was created, did, and had.

26:37.180 --> 26:48.460
And when you come to the darkness between the cycles, then you get both a flowering and a weeding out in what can survive that darkness.

26:48.460 --> 26:50.380
The darkness is going to change the form.

26:51.200 --> 27:06.460
In this sense, what we are talking about is the potential for a good telepathy that became realized to the point that it was necessary.

27:06.720 --> 27:17.340
It was a necessary channel for the Brynn and for the dancers who lacked the gifts to come upon them rather all at once.

27:17.340 --> 27:25.800
And lack the ability to control them at first, then you become a situation where you are a symbiont.

27:26.620 --> 27:28.560
But not in the normal physical sense.

27:29.060 --> 27:30.120
They can live separately.

27:30.480 --> 27:31.440
You can fuse it separately.

27:31.660 --> 27:32.860
You can interrelate it and it will lose itself.

27:34.380 --> 27:43.660
They, to be, to reach anything approaching their fullest potential, they must be cared.

27:44.780 --> 27:53.740
However, not all Brynn's and not all Vignasi are dancers and the ones who aren't are the basic key to the restaurant.

27:55.140 --> 27:59.240
There are many unanswered questions remaining after three installments with the Fire Dancer series.

27:59.680 --> 28:01.860
We asked Maxwell if she plans to wrap it up soon.

28:01.860 --> 28:08.480
I must say that I would never in one sense totally resolve the dancer thing.

28:08.660 --> 28:16.160
In other words, even if they do achieve some of Riza's goals, that is a beginning as well as an ending.

28:16.840 --> 28:26.040
If you have a whole new planet of dancers plus the residue of slaves and talents from the planet Lou,

28:26.040 --> 28:35.200
you are going to have a world once again that is dynamic, that evokes sympathy of the past rather than just a moment.

28:36.980 --> 28:41.300
And Maxwell has presented science fiction with two very interesting yet quite different series.

28:41.800 --> 28:43.180
